  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Legal Support Specialist",
  "description": "<p>We are looking for a Legal Support Specialist to support a regional Legal Country Team within a leading financial services organization. The role focuses on legal operations, litigation support, risk and controls, and stakeholder coordination, requiring strong attention to detail and the ability to manage multiple priorities in a fast-paced environment.</p><p>The ideal candidate will develop a strong understanding of the organization’s legal processes, policies, risk framework, and control environment, while working closely with senior stakeholders across business and functional teams.</p><p><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Support legal operations including technology, budgeting, expenses, and administrative activities</li><li>Assist in litigation and legal action intake, tracking, reporting, and settlements</li><li>Support risk and control monitoring, ensuring compliance with internal policies and procedures</li><li>Coordinate with cross-functional stakeholders (Legal, Compliance, Finance, Operations) on initiatives and projects</li><li>Manage legal invoicing and settlement payments</li><li>Perform analysis to support decision-making and resolution of legal matters</li><li>Handle multiple work requests with tight deadlines while maintaining high quality standards</li><li>Escalate and report control issues transparently and in line with governance requirement</li></ul><p><strong>Required Experience & Qualifications</strong><br /><br />2–5 years of relevant experience in:</p><ul><li>Corporate legal department</li><li>Law firm</li><li>Financial services / banking</li><li>Consulting or related industry</li></ul><p><u><strong>Education:</strong></u></p><ul><li>Bachelors/University degree or equivalent experience</li></ul><p>The work loacation is at CBP.</p>",
